abstract: A lawyer for Nike testified Thursday that he felt like a stickup victim when well-known attorney Michael Avenatti demanded up to $25 million to stop him from igniting a media scandal by publicizing claims that Nike employees paid the families of elite high school basketball players.

lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — A lawyer for Nike testified Thursday that he felt like a stickup victim when well-known attorney Michael Avenatti demanded up to $25 million to stop him from igniting a media scandal by publicizing claims that Nike employees paid the families of elite high school basketball players.
headline_main: Nike Lawyer: Avenatti Threatened Nike With 'Media Scandal'
headline_print_headline: Nike Lawyer: Avenatti Threatened Nike With 'Media Scandal'

abstract: Senator Rand Paul, Republican of Kentucky, read the name to reporters and posted it on Twitter after failing to get Chief Justice John G. Roberts Jr. to say during President Trump’s impeachment trial.
snippet: Senator Rand Paul, Republican of Kentucky, read the name to reporters and posted it on Twitter after failing to get Chief Justice John G. Roberts Jr. to say during President Trump’s impeachment trial.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Rand Paul clashed publicly on Thursday with Chief Justice John G. Roberts Jr. after the Kentucky Republican tried and failed to ask a question at President Trump’s impeachment trial that would have named the person widely thought to be the whistle-blower whose complaint formed the basis for the charges.

abstract: The first part of Thursday’s session focused largely on the arguments of one of President Trump’s lawyers, Alan M. Dershowitz.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The clock wound down on Thursday as senators posed questions to impeachment trial lawyers in an effort to consider whether to remove President Trump from office.

headline_main: Six Takeaways From Senators’ Questions to Impeachment Lawyers

abstract: He has quickly emerged as one of President Trump’s leading defenders on the Senate floor.
snippet: He has quickly emerged as one of President Trump’s leading defenders on the Senate floor.
lead_paragraph: Patrick Philbin, a deputy White House counsel, has quickly emerged as one of President Trump’s leading defenders on the Senate floor, jumping up to answer some of the most pointed questions from senators. His last name quickly drew jokes about whether Mr. Trump, with his love of television, confused the lawyer with the television host who shares the same surname — but his background is in fact far more significant.

abstract: Until late Thursday, Mr. Romney was the only Republican senator calling for witnesses in the impeachment trial. His G.O.P. colleagues are taking shots: One branded him “Jeff Flake on steroids.”
snippet: Until late Thursday, Mr. Romney was the only Republican senator calling for witnesses in the impeachment trial. His G.O.P. colleagues are taking shots: One branded him “Jeff Flake on steroids.”
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — It’s been one of those spectacle weeks on Capitol Hill, the likes of which history might just stop to recognize, even if Trump-era Washington pauses for nothing.

headline_print_headline: Standing Alone, At Center of It All

abstract: The commerce secretary just flunked microbe economics.
snippet: The commerce secretary just flunked microbe economics.
lead_paragraph: How frightened should you be about the coronavirus? I’m no epidemiologist, but what I’ve seen looks pretty scary. It doesn’t help that the Trump administration, as part of its general war against science and expertise, has seriously reduced America’s capacity to respond if we do face a dangerous pandemic.

abstract: Chief Justice John Roberts is the picture of judicial modesty at President Donald Trump's impeachment trial, wearing his unadorned black robe and wielding an ivory gavel as he presides over the Senate.
snippet: Chief Justice John Roberts is the picture of judicial modesty at President Donald Trump's impeachment trial, wearing his unadorned black robe and wielding an ivory gavel as he presides over the Senate.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Chief Justice John Roberts is the picture of judicial modesty at President Donald Trump's impeachment trial, wearing his unadorned black robe and wielding an ivory gavel as he presides over the Senate.
headline_main: Gavel Time: Will Chief Justice Expand His Impeachment Role?

abstract: Proposed tweaks to the Volcker Rule, which curbs bank risk-taking, would allow firms to invest heavily in funds backing start-ups.
snippet: Proposed tweaks to the Volcker Rule, which curbs bank risk-taking, would allow firms to invest heavily in funds backing start-ups.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Banks could invest heavily in or even sponsor venture capital funds under a proposed change to a post-crisis rule that was intended to limit their risk-taking.
